In the case of the "Typewriter" animation, characters are revealed one by one, and there isn't a simple way to calculate the width of the partially revealed text since sourceRectAtTime() would give you the dimensions of the entire text box, not just the visible part.

However, you can still estimate the width of the visible part of the text by multiplying the width of the full text with the percentage of the text that's supposed to be visible at that specific time. This requires you to know the timing of your animator.

